&gt;       With the RS hacks they are basically just opening the case carefully and cutting the mute wire or pulling out the mute pin depending whichradio it is. Check the archives for descriptions for each model. RS updated some versions of the radios so they were no longer able to be modified. Steve Hultay went on to try it on a few other radios and got some good results. 
&gt; 
&gt; You can also do a manual sweep with a radio that has a knob/dial or a scan function that doesnt jump the stations too quickly by simply scanning across the band. This method works great.
